<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="uz">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>English Grammar in Use — To'liq Test</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Source+Sans+3:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root{
    --bg: #EAF1EF;
    --bg-deep: #DCE8E5;
    --surface: #FFFFFF;
    --surface-soft: #F4F8F7;
    --ink: #16292A;
    --ink-soft: #4C6668;
    --ink-faint: #7C9294;
    --teal: #0F4C4F;
    --teal-deep: #093435;
    --teal-tint: #DDEBEA;
    --coral: #D2483A;
    --coral-deep: #AC3629;
    --coral-tint: #FBE3DF;
    --green: #2C7A54;
    --green-deep: #1F5D40;
    --green-tint: #DCEFE3;
    --gold: #B9822E;
    --gold-tint: #F5E9D3;
    --border: #C9D9D6;
    --shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(15,76,79,0.06), 0 8px 24px -12px rgba(15,76,79,0.22);
    --radius-sm: 8px;
    --radius-md: 14px;
    --radius-lg: 22px;
    --font-display: 'Space Grotesk', 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    --font-body: 'Source Sans 3', 'Source Sans Pro', 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
  }

  *{ box-sizing: border-box; }

  html,body{
    margin:0;
    padding:0;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  #app{
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 28px 20px 80px;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px){
    #app{ padding: 44px 32px 100px; }
  }

  ::selection{ background: var(--coral-tint); color: var(--coral-deep); }

  button{ font-family: inherit; cursor: pointer; }
  a{ color: inherit; }

  .sr-only{
    position:absolute; width:1px; height:1px; padding:0; margin:-1px;
    overflow:hidden; clip:rect(0,0,0,0); white-space:nowrap; border:0;
  }

  /* ---------- Masthead ---------- */
  .masthead{
    display:flex;
    align-items:flex-start;
    justify-content:space-between;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .masthead-brand{
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    gap:10px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight:600;
    font-size: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
  }
  .masthead-brand .mark{
    width: 28px; height:28px;
    border-radius: 7px;
    background: var(--teal);
    color: #fff;
    display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight:700;
    flex-shrink:0;
  }
  .masthead-score{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    text-align:right;
    line-height:1.4;
  }
  .masthead-score b{ color: var(--teal); font-size:16px; }

  /* ---------- Hero ---------- */
  .hero{
    background: var(--teal);
    color: #EFF6F5;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 34px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .hero::after{
    content:"";
    position:absolute;
    right:-60px; top:-60px;
    width:220px; height:220px;
    border-radius:50%;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(210,72,58,0.35), transparent 70%);
  }
  .hero-eyebrow{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 12.5px;
    letter-spacing: 0.09em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--coral-tint);
    opacity:0.85;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    position:relative;
  }
  .hero h1{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(26px, 5vw, 38px);
    line-height: 1.12;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    position:relative;
  }
  .hero p{
    font-size: 15.5px;
    line-height:1.55;
    color: #D3E6E3;
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin: 0 0 22px;
    position:relative;
  }
  .hero-stats{
    display:flex;
    gap: 22px;
    flex-wrap:wrap;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    position:relative;
  }
  .hero-stat b{
    display:block;
    font-family:var(--font-display);
    font-size: 22px;
    color:#fff;
  }
  .hero-stat span{
    font-size: 12px;
    color: #AFC9C5;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing:0.05em;
  }
  .btn{
    display:inline-flex;
    align-items:center;
    gap:8px;
    border:none;
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 14px 26px;
    font-size: 15.5px;
    font-weight:600;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    transition: transform 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.15s ease, background 0.15s ease;
  }
  .btn:active{ transform: scale(0.97); }
  .btn-primary{
    background: var(--coral);
    color: #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 24px -10px rgba(210,72,58,0.7);
    position:relative;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover{ background: var(--coral-deep); }
  .btn-ghost{
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
    color: #fff;
    border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.35);
  }
  .btn-ghost:hover{ background: rgba(255,255,255,0.2); }
  .btn-secondary{
    background: var(--surface);
    color: var(--teal);
    border:1.5px solid var(--border);
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover{ border-color: var(--teal); }
  .btn-block{ width:100%; justify-content:center; }
  .btn-row{ display:flex; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap; }

  /* ---------- Section list on home ---------- */
  .section-list-label{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 13px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 30px 0 12px;
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    justify-content:space-between;
  }
  .card-grid{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  @media (min-width:560px){
    .card-grid{ grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
  .section-card{
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 16px 16px;
    text-align:left;
    display:flex;
    gap:12px;
    align-items:flex-start;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, transform 0.15s ease;
  }
  .section-card:hover{
    border-color: var(--teal);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  .section-tag{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight:700;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--teal);
    background: var(--teal-tint);
    border-radius: 7px;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    white-space:nowrap;
    flex-shrink:0;
    min-width: 54px;
    text-align:center;
  }
  .section-card.is-vocab .section-tag{
    color: var(--coral-deep);
    background: var(--coral-tint);
  }
  .section-card-body{ flex:1; min-width:0; }
  .section-card-title{
    font-weight:600;
    font-size: 15px;
    margin: 0 0 2px;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .section-card-sub{
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .section-card-meta{
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    gap:8px;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }
  .score-pill{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight:700;
    font-size: 11.5px;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 999px;
  }
  .score-pill.great{ background: var(--green-tint); color: var(--green-deep); }
  .score-pill.ok{ background: var(--gold-tint); color: var(--gold); }
  .score-pill.low{ background: var(--coral-tint); color: var(--coral-deep); }

  /* ---------- Quiz screen ---------- */
  .quiz-topbar{
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    justify-content:space-between;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .back-btn{
    background:none; border:none;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 14px;
    display:flex; align-items:center; gap:6px;
    padding: 6px 4px;
  }
  .back-btn:hover{ color: var(--teal); }
  .progress-track{
    flex:1;
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--bg-deep);
    border-radius: 999px;
    margin: 0 14px;
    overflow:hidden;
  }
  .progress-fill{
    height:100%;
    background: var(--coral);
    border-radius:999px;
    transition: width 0.25s ease;
  }
  .progress-count{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    white-space:nowrap;
  }

  .q-card{
    background: var(--surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 26px 22px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .q-unit-row{
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    gap:10px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .q-unit-badge{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight:700;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--teal);
    color:#fff;
    padding: 5px 10px;
    border-radius: 7px;
    letter-spacing:0.02em;
  }
  .q-unit-title{
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    line-height:1.3;
  }
  .q-prompt{
    font-size: clamp(18px, 3.6vw, 21px);
    line-height:1.5;
    font-weight:500;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 22px;
  }
  .q-prompt .blank{
    display:inline-block;
    min-width: 44px;
    border-bottom: 2.5px solid var(--coral);
    color:transparent;
  }
  .options{
    display:flex;
    flex-direction:column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .option{
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    gap:12px;
    text-align:left;
    background: var(--surface-soft);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 13px 15px;
    font-size: 15.5px;
    color: var(--ink);
    transition: border-color 0.12s ease, background 0.12s ease;
  }
  .option:hover:not(.locked){
    border-color: var(--teal);
    background: #fff;
  }
  .option .letter{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight:700;
    font-size:13px;
    width: 26px; height:26px;
    border-radius:50%;
    background: var(--bg-deep);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    flex-shrink:0;
  }
  .option .mark{
    margin-left:auto;
    font-size:17px;
    flex-shrink:0;
    line-height:1;
  }
  .option.correct{
    background: var(--green-tint);
    border-color: var(--green);
    color: var(--green-deep);
  }
  .option.correct .letter{ background: var(--green); color:#fff; }
  .option.wrong{
    background: var(--coral-tint);
    border-color: var(--coral);
    color: var(--coral-deep);
  }
  .option.wrong .letter{ background: var(--coral); color:#fff; }
  .option.dim{ opacity: 0.55; }

  .explain{
    margin-top: 18px;
    padding: 15px 16px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    background: var(--teal-tint);
    border-left: 3.5px solid var(--teal);
    font-size: 14.5px;
    line-height:1.55;
    color: var(--teal-deep);
    animation: slideIn 0.25s ease;
  }
  .explain b{ color: var(--teal); }

  @keyframes slideIn{
    from{ opacity:0; transform: translateY(-6px); }
    to{ opacity:1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  .q-footer{
    margin-top: 20px;
    display:flex;
    justify-content:flex-end;
  }

  /* ---------- Interstitial / summary screens ---------- */
  .summary-card{
    background: var(--surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 32px 26px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    text-align:center;
  }
  .summary-ring{
    width: 128px; height:128px;
    border-radius:50%;
    margin: 0 auto 18px;
    display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center;
    flex-direction:column;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    background: conic-gradient(var(--teal) calc(var(--pct) * 1%), var(--bg-deep) 0);
    position:relative;
  }
  .summary-ring::before{
    content:"";
    position:absolute;
    inset:9px;
    border-radius:50%;
    background: var(--surface);
  }
  .summary-ring b{
    font-size: 30px;
    color: var(--ink);
    position:relative;
  }
  .summary-ring span{
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    position:relative;
  }
  .summary-card h2{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 22px;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
  }
  .summary-card p.lead{
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 14.5px;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }

  .mini-bars{
    display:flex;
    flex-direction:column;
    gap: 10px;
    text-align:left;
    margin: 18px 0 6px;
  }
  .mini-bar-row{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 46px;
    align-items:center;
    gap:10px;
  }
  .mini-bar-label{
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .mini-bar-label b{ color: var(--ink); font-weight:600; }
  .mini-bar-track{
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    height: 8px;
    background: var(--bg-deep);
    border-radius:999px;
    overflow:hidden;
    margin-top: -4px;
  }
  .mini-bar-fill{
    height:100%;
    border-radius:999px;
    background: var(--teal);
  }
  .mini-bar-pct{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size:12.5px;
    font-weight:700;
    text-align:right;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .review-list{
    text-align:left;
    background: var(--surface-soft);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 16px 18px;
    margin: 20px 0;
    border: 1px dashed var(--border);
  }
  .review-list h3{
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 13.5px;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    letter-spacing:0.04em;
    color: var(--coral-deep);
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }
  .review-chip{
    display:inline-flex;
    align-items:center;
    gap:6px;
    background:#fff;
    border:1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius:999px;
    padding: 5px 10px 5px 6px;
    font-size:12.5px;
    margin: 0 6px 6px 0;
  }
  .review-chip .num{
    background: var(--coral);
    color:#fff;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight:700;
    font-size:11px;
    border-radius:50%;
    width:20px;height:20px;
    display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
  }

  .missed-detail{
    text-align:left;
    margin: 18px 0;
    display:flex;
    flex-direction:column;
    gap:12px;
  }
  .missed-item{
    background: var(--surface-soft);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--coral);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 12px 14px;
  }
  .missed-item .mi-q{ font-size:14px; margin-bottom:6px; color:var(--ink); }
  .missed-item .mi-a{ font-size:13px; color: var(--green-deep); margin-bottom:4px; }
  .missed-item .mi-a b{ color: var(--green-deep); }
  .missed-item .mi-e{ font-size:13px; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height:1.5; }

  footer.note{
    text-align:center;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    margin-top: 40px;
    line-height:1.6;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce){
    *{ animation-duration: 0.01ms !important; transition-duration: 0.01ms !important; }
  }
</style>
</head> <body>
<div id="app"></div>

<script>
const QUESTIONS = [{"id":"u1","unit":1,"section":"Present and past","unitTitle":"Present continuous (I am doing)","prompt":"Please be quiet. I ___ to concentrate on my work.","options":["try","am trying","tried","have tried"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Hozirgi paytda davom etayotgan harakat uchun Present Continuous (am/is/are + -ing) ishlatiladi. 'Hozir, gapirayotgan paytda' harakat davom etyapti — shuning uchun 'am trying'."},{"id":"u2","unit":2,"section":"Present and past","unitTitle":"Present simple (I do)","prompt":"Water ___ at 100 degrees Celsius.","options":["is boiling","boil","boils","boiled"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Doimiy haqiqatlar va umumiy faktlar uchun Present Simple ishlatiladi. Uchinchi shaxs birlikda (water = it) fe'lga -s qo'shiladi: boils."},{"id":"u3","unit":3,"section":"Present and past","unitTitle":"Present continuous and present simple 1","prompt":"Look! That man ___ to open the door of your car.","options":["tries","is trying","try","has tried"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Look!' so'zi hozir, aynan shu daqiqada sodir bo'layotgan harakatni bildiradi, shuning uchun Present Continuous kerak, doimiy odat emas."},{"id":"u4","unit":4,"section":"Present and past","unitTitle":"Present continuous and present simple 2","prompt":"I ___ what you mean, but I don't agree with you.","options":["am seeing","see","am seen","saw"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'See' (tushunmoq ma'nosida), 'know', 'like', 'want' kabi fe'llar holatni bildiradi (state verbs) va odatda Continuous formada ishlatilmaydi."},{"id":"u5","unit":5,"section":"Present and past","unitTitle":"Past simple (I did)","prompt":"We ___ to the cinema last Friday.","options":["go","have gone","went","were going"],"correct":2,"explanation":"'Last Friday' — tugallangan, aniq o'tgan payt belgisi, shuning uchun Past Simple (went) ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u6","unit":6,"section":"Present and past","unitTitle":"Past continuous (I was doing)","prompt":"I saw Helen at the party. She ___ a really nice dress.","options":["wore","was wearing","is wearing","wears"],"correct":1,"explanation":"O'tgan paytda davom etayotgan holatni tasvirlash uchun Past Continuous (was/were + -ing) ishlatiladi — o'sha payt kiyimda edi."},{"id":"u7","unit":7,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"Present perfect 1 (I have done)","prompt":"'Have you ever been to Japan?' 'No, I ___ there.'","options":["never went","have never been","never was","am never being"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Umr davomidagi tajriba (aniq vaqt ko'rsatilmagan) haqida gapirganda Present Perfect (have/has + V3) ishlatiladi: have never been."},{"id":"u8","unit":8,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"Present perfect 2 (I have done)","prompt":"Sarah ___ her keys. She can't get into her flat.","options":["lost","has lost","loses","was losing"],"correct":1,"explanation":"O'tmishdagi harakat hozirgi natijaga ega bo'lsa (kalitlarni yo'qotgani hozir ta'sir qilyapti), Present Perfect ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u9","unit":9,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"Present perfect continuous (I have been doing)","prompt":"You're out of breath. ___ ?","options":["Did you run","Have you been running","Are you running","Do you run"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Yaqinda tugagan, lekin natijasi hozir ko'rinib turgan davomli harakat uchun Present Perfect Continuous (have been + -ing) ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u10","unit":10,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"Present perfect continuous and simple","prompt":"She ___ six cups of coffee today (and it's only midday!).","options":["has been drinking","has drunk","is drinking","drank"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Nechta/qancha (how many/how much) — natija muhim bo'lganda Present Perfect Simple ishlatiladi, davomiylik emas: has drunk six cups."},{"id":"u11","unit":11,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"how long have you (been) …?","prompt":"How long ___ each other?","options":["do you know","have you known","are you knowing","did you know"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Know' holat fe'li bo'lgani uchun Continuous emas, Present Perfect Simple bilan 'How long have you known...?' deyiladi."},{"id":"u12","unit":12,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"for and since when …? and how long …?","prompt":"I haven't seen Tom ___ Monday.","options":["for","since","from","during"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Aniq boshlanish nuqtasi (Monday) ko'rsatilganda 'since' ishlatiladi; 'for' esa davomiylik/muddat bilan ishlatiladi (for three days)."},{"id":"u13","unit":13,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"Present perfect and past 1","prompt":"'Is Sarah here?' 'No, she ___ out.'","options":["has gone","went","is going","has been going"],"correct":0,"explanation":"Aniq o'tgan vaqt aytilmagan, hozirgi holatga (u hozir yo'q) ta'sir qiladi — shuning uchun Present Perfect: has gone out."},{"id":"u14","unit":14,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"Present perfect and past 2","prompt":"I ___ this book yesterday evening.","options":["have finished","finished","have been finishing","was finishing"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Yesterday evening' — aniq, tugallangan o'tgan payt, shu sababli Present Perfect emas, Past Simple ishlatiladi: finished."},{"id":"u15","unit":15,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"Past perfect (I had done)","prompt":"When I arrived at the party, Kate ___ already ___.","options":["has / left","had / left","was / leaving","did / leave"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Ikkita o'tgan harakatdan oldingisi uchun Past Perfect (had + V3) ishlatiladi: Kate kelishimdan OLDIN ketgan edi — had left."},{"id":"u16","unit":16,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"Past perfect continuous (I had been doing)","prompt":"Sam was tired when he got home. He ___ all day.","options":["was working","had been working","has been working","worked"],"correct":1,"explanation":"O'tgan paytdagi holatdan OLDIN davom etgan harakat uchun Past Perfect Continuous (had been + -ing) ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u17","unit":17,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"have and have got","prompt":"Choose the correct alternative: 'Do you have a car?' means the same as ___","options":["Have you a car?","Have you got a car?","Are you having a car?","Have you had a car?"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Have got' — 'have'ning ingliz tilida keng tarqalgan so'zlashuv sinonimi: Have you got a car? = Do you have a car?"},{"id":"u18","unit":18,"section":"Present perfect and past","unitTitle":"used to (do)","prompt":"I ___ live in London, but I moved to Bristol a few years ago.","options":["use to","used to","am used to","was using"],"correct":1,"explanation":"O'tmishda muntazam bo'lib, hozir bo'lmaydigan odat/holat haqida gapirganda 'used to + infinitive' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u19","unit":19,"section":"Future","unitTitle":"Present tenses for the future","prompt":"What time ___ tomorrow evening?","options":["will your train arrive","does your train arrive","is your train arriving","your train arrives"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Kelajakdagi rejalashtirilgan jadval/dastur (poezd jadvali) uchun Present Continuous ishlatilishi mumkin: is arriving."},{"id":"u20","unit":20,"section":"Future","unitTitle":"I'm going to (do)","prompt":"I feel terrible. I think I ___ sick.","options":["will be","am going to be","am being","be"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Hozirgi holatga qarab kelajakda nima bo'lishini aytib bo'ladigan holatlar uchun 'be going to' ishlatiladi (alomatlar hozir bor)."},{"id":"u21","unit":21,"section":"Future","unitTitle":"will and shall 1","prompt":"I'm too tired to walk home. I think I ___ a taxi.","options":["am getting","get","will get","am going to getting"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Gapirish paytida qaror qilinayotgan (spontan) kelajak reja uchun 'will' ishlatiladi: I think I'll get a taxi."},{"id":"u22","unit":22,"section":"Future","unitTitle":"will and shall 2","prompt":"___ I open the window? It's a bit hot in here.","options":["Will","Shall","Do","Am"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Taklif qilish yoki ruxsat so'rash uchun 'Shall I …?' qolipi ishlatiladi (Shall I open…? = Xohlaysizmi men ochsam?)."},{"id":"u23","unit":23,"section":"Future","unitTitle":"I will and I'm going to","prompt":"a: 'Did you post that letter for me?' b: 'Oh, sorry, I completely forgot. ___ now.'","options":["I'm going to do it","I'll do it","I do it","I'm doing it"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Gapirish payti qaror qilingan tezkor va'da/qaror uchun 'will' ishlatiladi, oldindan rejalashtirilgan 'going to' emas."},{"id":"u24","unit":24,"section":"Future","unitTitle":"will be doing and will have done","prompt":"Don't phone at 8.30 — I ___ dinner then.","options":["will have","will be having","have","will having"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Kelajakda ma'lum bir vaqtda davom etayotgan harakat uchun Future Continuous (will be + -ing) ishlatiladi: will be having dinner."},{"id":"u25","unit":25,"section":"Future","unitTitle":"when I do and when I've done / if and when","prompt":"I'll call you as soon as I ___ home.","options":["will get","get","am getting","will have got"],"correct":1,"explanation":"When/as soon as/before kabi vaqt bog'lovchilaridan keyingi ergash gapda kelajak uchun 'will' emas, Present Simple ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u26","unit":26,"section":"Modals","unitTitle":"can, could and (be) able to","prompt":"I used to ___ stand on my head when I was a child, but I can't do it now.","options":["can","could","be able to","being able to"],"correct":1,"explanation":"O'tmishdagi umumiy qobiliyat haqida 'could' ishlatiladi. Bitta muvaffaqiyatli holat uchun esa 'was able to' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u27","unit":27,"section":"Modals","unitTitle":"could (do) and could have (done)","prompt":"Why didn't you come to the party? You ___ a great time.","options":["could have","could","can have","can"],"correct":0,"explanation":"O'tmishda bajarilmagan imkoniyat haqida afsuslanishda 'could have + V3' ishlatiladi: could have had a great time."},{"id":"u28","unit":28,"sectio