 qoladi, lekin fe'l -ing shaklida qoladi: no point calling."},{"id":"u64","unit":64,"section":"-ing and to …","unitTitle":"to …, for … and so that …","prompt":"I'm saving money ___ buy a new car.","options":["for","so that","to","for to"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Maqsadni bildirish uchun oddiy infinitiv (to + fe'l) ishlatiladi: to buy. 'For' esa keyin ot (noun) yoki -ing keladi."},{"id":"u65","unit":65,"section":"-ing and to …","unitTitle":"Adjective + to …","prompt":"I was disappointed ___ that Kate couldn't come to the party.","options":["hearing","to hear","hear","for hear"],"correct":1,"explanation":"His-tuyg'u bildiruvchi sifatlardan (disappointed, glad, surprised) keyin infinitiv keladi: disappointed to hear."},{"id":"u66","unit":66,"section":"-ing and to …","unitTitle":"to … (afraid to do) and preposition + -ing (afraid of -ing)","prompt":"I like the people I work with, but I'm not afraid ___ my opinion if I disagree with them.","options":["of giving","to give","give","of give"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Afraid to do' — jasorat kerak bo'lgan harakatni bajarishdan tortinish: afraid to give (fikrimni aytishdan qo'rqmayman)."},{"id":"u67","unit":67,"section":"-ing and to …","unitTitle":"see somebody do and see somebody doing","prompt":"I saw Kate ___ across the road just before the accident happened.","options":["walking","to walk","walked","walks"],"correct":0,"explanation":"Harakatning bir qismini/jarayonini ko'rganda 'see somebody doing' (-ing) ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u68","unit":68,"section":"-ing and to …","unitTitle":"-ing clauses (He hurt his knee playing football.)","prompt":"___ for the bus, I saw an old friend of mine.","options":["While waiting","While I wait","During waiting","For waiting"],"correct":0,"explanation":"Ikki harakat bir vaqtda bir subyekt tomonidan bajarilganda, qisqartirilgan -ing gap ishlatiladi: While waiting (kutayotganimda)."},{"id":"u69","unit":69,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"Countable and uncountable 1","prompt":"Can I have ___ , please?","options":["an information","some informations","some information","informations"],"correct":2,"explanation":"'Information' — sanalmaydigan ot (uncountable), ko'plik shakli yo'q va 'a/an' bilan ishlatilmaydi: some information."},{"id":"u70","unit":70,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"Countable and uncountable 2","prompt":"I'd like ___ bread, please.","options":["a","a piece of","one","the piece"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Sanalmaydigan otni sanash uchun maxsus so'z birikmasi kerak: a piece of bread."},{"id":"u71","unit":71,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"Countable nouns with a/an and some","prompt":"There's ___ orange in the fridge if you're hungry.","options":["a","an","some","the"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Orange' unli tovush bilan boshlanadi, shuning uchun 'a' emas, 'an' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u72","unit":72,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"a/an and the","prompt":"I bought ___ shirt yesterday, but ___ shirt was too small.","options":["a / the","the / a","a / a","the / the"],"correct":0,"explanation":"Birinchi marta tilga olinganda 'a' (noaniq artikl), keyin xuddi shu narsa haqida gapirganda 'the' (aniq artikl) ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u73","unit":73,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"the 1","prompt":"___ sun is a star.","options":["A","--(no article)","The","An"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Dunyoda yagona bo'lgan narsalar (the sun, the moon, the world) doim 'the' bilan ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u74","unit":74,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"the 2 (school / the school)","prompt":"Tom's brother is in prison. Tom often goes to ___ to visit him.","options":["the prison","prison","a prison","prisons"],"correct":0,"explanation":"Bu yerda maqsad qamoqxonaga TASHRIF buyurish, mahbus sifatida borish emas — shu sababli 'the prison' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u75","unit":75,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"the 3 (children / the children)","prompt":"___ life is impossible without water.","options":["The life","Life","A life","Lives"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Umumiy ma'noda (barcha hayot haqida) gapirganda sanalmaydigan otdan oldin artikl qo'yilmaydi: Life (umuman)."},{"id":"u76","unit":76,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"the 4 (the giraffe / the telephone / the old)","prompt":"___ giraffe is the tallest of all animals.","options":["A","--(no article)","The","Some"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Butun bir turni (hayvon turi sifatida) umumlashtirib gapirganda 'the + birlik ot' ishlatilishi mumkin: The giraffe."},{"id":"u77","unit":77,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"Names with and without the 1","prompt":"Have you ever been to ___ United States?","options":["--(no article)","a","the","an"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Respublika/shtatlar birlashmasini bildiruvchi davlat nomlari (United States, UK, Netherlands) 'the' bilan ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u78","unit":78,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"Names with and without the 2","prompt":"We visited ___ Louvre when we were in Paris.","options":["a","the","--(no article)","an"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Muzey, teatr, galereya kabi jamoat binolarining aksariyat nomlari 'the' bilan ishlatiladi: the Louvre."},{"id":"u79","unit":79,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"Singular and plural","prompt":"Police ___ investigating the robbery.","options":["is","are","was","has been"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Police' so'zi shaklan birlik bo'lsada, ma'nosi ko'plik va ko'plik fe'l bilan ishlatiladi: police are."},{"id":"u80","unit":80,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"Noun + noun (a bus driver / a headache)","prompt":"We waited at the ___ stop for twenty minutes.","options":["buses","bus's","bus","bus'"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Ikki ot yonma-yon kelib birikma hosil qilganda, birinchi ot odatda birlikda qoladi: bus stop."},{"id":"u81","unit":81,"section":"Articles and nouns","unitTitle":"-'s and of …","prompt":"What's ___ ?","options":["the name of this street","this street's name","the street name of","of this street the name"],"correct":0,"explanation":"Jonsiz narsalar uchun ('s emas) 'of' konstruksiyasi ko'proq ishlatiladi: the name of this street."},{"id":"u82","unit":82,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"myself/yourself/themselves etc.","prompt":"Kate hurt ___ while she was playing tennis.","options":["her","herself","hers","she"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Harakatning ta'siri gap egasining o'ziga qaytganda refleksiv olmosh ishlatiladi: hurt herself."},{"id":"u83","unit":83,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"a friend of mine, my own house, on my own/by myself","prompt":"I'd like to have ___ apartment instead of sharing with roommates.","options":["a mine","my own","the own","of my own an"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'my own + ot' — 'faqat menga tegishli' ma'nosini beradi: my own apartment."},{"id":"u84","unit":84,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"there … and it …","prompt":"'What's the weather like today?' '___ raining.'","options":["There's","It's","This is","That's"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Ob-havo haqida gapirganda gap egasi sifatida 'it' ishlatiladi: It's raining."},{"id":"u85","unit":85,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"some and any","prompt":"I didn't have ___ money, so I couldn't buy anything.","options":["some","any","no","much a"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Salbiy gaplarda odatda 'some' emas, 'any' ishlatiladi: didn't have any money."},{"id":"u86","unit":86,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"no/none/any, nothing/nobody etc.","prompt":"'How much money have you got?' '___ .'","options":["No","Any","None","Not any"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Savolga qisqa javob berishda ('nothing' ma'nosida) 'none' mustaqil ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u87","unit":87,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"much, many, little, few, a lot, plenty","prompt":"She's very busy these days. She's got very ___ free time.","options":["few","a few","little","a little"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Sanalmaydigan otlar bilan 'kam/deyarli yo'q' ma'nosida 'little' ishlatiladi (salbiy ohang): little free time."},{"id":"u88","unit":88,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"all/all of, most/most of, no/none of etc.","prompt":"___ of the people at the party were friends of Andy's.","options":["Most","Almost","Mostly","The most"],"correct":0,"explanation":"'Most of + the/these/my ...' qolipida aniqlovchidan oldin 'most' ishlatiladi (almost emas): Most of the people."},{"id":"u89","unit":89,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"both/both of, neither/neither of, either/either of","prompt":"___ of us was hungry, so we didn't eat anything.","options":["Both","Neither","All","None"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Ikki narsa/kishi haqida salbiy ma'noda gapirganda 'neither' (ikkalasi ham ...emas) ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u90","unit":90,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"all, every, whole","prompt":"I've spent the ___ day cleaning the house.","options":["every","all","whole","each"],"correct":2,"explanation":"'The whole + birlik ot' — butun/hammasi ma'nosida: the whole day (butun kun)."},{"id":"u91","unit":91,"section":"Pronouns and determiners","unitTitle":"each and every","prompt":"___ time I see you, you look different!","options":["Every","All","Each of","Whole"],"correct":0,"explanation":"'Every time' — sodir bo'ladigan har safar ma'nosida keng qo'llaniladigan ibora."},{"id":"u92","unit":92,"section":"Relative clauses","unitTitle":"Relative clauses 1: who/that/which","prompt":"The woman ___ lives next door is a doctor.","options":["she","who","whom","what"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Odam haqida gapirganda va nisbiy gapda ega (subject) o'rnida 'who' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u93","unit":93,"section":"Relative clauses","unitTitle":"Relative clauses 2: with and without who/that/which","prompt":"Where's the money ___ I gave you?","options":["who","--(can be left out)","whose","--(cannot be left out)"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Nisbiy olmosh gapda TO'LDIRUVCHI (object) vazifasini bajarsa, ko'pincha tushirib qoldirilishi mumkin: the money (that/which) I gave you."},{"id":"u94","unit":94,"section":"Relative clauses","unitTitle":"Relative clauses 3: whose/whom/where","prompt":"That's the woman ___ car was stolen last week.","options":["who","whom","whose","which"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Egalik ma'nosini bildirish uchun ('uning mashinasi') 'whose' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u95","unit":95,"section":"Relative clauses","unitTitle":"Relative clauses 4: extra information clauses (1)","prompt":"My sister, ___ lives in Paris, is coming to visit next week.","options":["that","who","she who","--(no word)"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Qo'shimcha (ajratilgan, vergul bilan ajratilgan) ma'lumot beruvchi gapda 'that' emas, faqat 'who/which' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u96","unit":96,"section":"Relative clauses","unitTitle":"Relative clauses 5: extra information clauses (2)","prompt":"Amy showed me a photo of her son, ___ made me feel old.","options":["that","what","which","who"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Butun bir gapga izoh berish uchun (vergul bilan) 'which' ishlatiladi, aniq bir otga emas."},{"id":"u97","unit":97,"section":"Relative clauses","unitTitle":"-ing and -ed clauses","prompt":"Do you know the woman ___ to Andy over there?","options":["talks","talked","who talking","talking"],"correct":3,"explanation":"Hozir davom etayotgan harakatni qisqartirib tasvirlash uchun -ing gap ishlatiladi: the woman talking to Andy."},{"id":"u98","unit":98,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Adjectives ending in -ing and -ed (boring/bored)","prompt":"The lecture was so ___ that several students fell asleep.","options":["bored","boring","bore","bores"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Narsa/vaziyat qanday ta'sir qilishini bildirganda -ing shakli ishlatiladi: boring (zerikarli). -ed shakli esa kishining his-tuyg'usini bildiradi."},{"id":"u99","unit":99,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Adjectives: a nice new house, you look tired","prompt":"You look ___ . What's wrong?","options":["tiredly","tired","tiring","to tired"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Look/feel/seem' kabi fe'llardan keyin ravish emas, sifat keladi: look tired."},{"id":"u100","unit":100,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Adjectives and adverbs 1 (quick/quickly)","prompt":"She speaks English very ___ .","options":["good","well","goodly","best"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Fe'lni ('speaks') tavsiflash uchun ravish (adverb) kerak: 'good'ning ravishi — well."},{"id":"u101","unit":101,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Adjectives and adverbs 2 (well, fast, late, hard/hardly)","prompt":"I searched everywhere for my keys, but I could ___ find them.","options":["hard","hardly","hardly not","not hardly"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Hardly' — 'deyarli...emas' ma'nosidagi mustaqil ravish (hard'dan farqli): could hardly find (deyarli topolmadim)."},{"id":"u102","unit":102,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"so and such","prompt":"It was ___ a boring film that I fell asleep.","options":["so","such","so a","too"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Ot (film) oldida sifat bilan birga bo'lsa 'such a' ishlatiladi: such a boring film."},{"id":"u103","unit":103,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"enough and too","prompt":"This coffee is ___ hot for me to drink.","options":["too","enough","so","very"],"correct":0,"explanation":"'Ortiqcha darajada, salbiy natijaga olib keladigan' ma'noda 'too' ishlatiladi: too hot (juda issiq, icha olmayman)."},{"id":"u104","unit":104,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"quite, pretty, rather, fairly","prompt":"It's ___ cold today — you'd better wear a coat.","options":["quite","enough","too much","so"],"correct":0,"explanation":"O'rtacha darajadagi kuchaytiruvchi so'z sifatida 'quite' ishlatilishi mumkin: quite cold (anchagina sovuq)."},{"id":"u105","unit":105,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Comparative 1 (cheaper, more expensive)","prompt":"This exercise is ___ than the last one.","options":["more difficult","difficulter","more difficulter","most difficult"],"correct":0,"explanation":"Ikki-uch bo'g'inli va undan uzun sifatlarning qiyosiy darajasi 'more + sifat' orqali yasaladi: more difficult."},{"id":"u106","unit":106,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Comparative 2 (much better / any better)","prompt":"This bag is ___ bigger than the one I had before.","options":["very","much","more","so"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Qiyosiy darajani kuchaytirish uchun 'much/a lot/far' ishlatiladi, 'very' emas: much bigger."},{"id":"u107","unit":107,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Comparative 3 (as … as / than)","prompt":"I don't earn ___ money as you.","options":["as much","as many","so much as","as such"],"correct":0,"explanation":"Sanalmaydigan otlar bilan tenglik/qiyoslash uchun 'as much + ot + as' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u108","unit":108,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Superlative (the longest, the most enjoyable)","prompt":"It was ___ day of my life.","options":["more happy","the happiest","happiest","most happy"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Orttirma daraja odatda 'the' bilan ishlatiladi: the happiest day."},{"id":"u109","unit":109,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Word order 1: verb + object; place and time","prompt":"Choose the correctly ordered sentence.","options":["I bought yesterday a new phone.","I bought a new phone yesterday.","Yesterday I a new phone bought.","I a new phone bought yesterday."],"correct":1,"explanation":"Fe'l + to'ldiruvchi odatda birga keladi, ular orasiga vaqt/o'rin qo'yilmaydi: bought a new phone yesterday."},{"id":"u110","unit":110,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"Word order 2: adverbs with the verb","prompt":"I ___ drink coffee in the evening.","options":["never almost","almost never","never much","much never"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Chastota ravishlari (always/often/never) yordamchi fe'l bo'lmasa, asosiy fe'ldan OLDIN keladi: almost never drink."},{"id":"u111","unit":111,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"still, any more/yet/already","prompt":"Are you ___ working for the same company, or have you changed jobs?","options":["yet","already","still","any more"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Bir holat kutilganidan uzoqroq davom etayotganini bildirish uchun 'still' ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u112","unit":112,"section":"Adjectives and adverbs","unitTitle":"even","prompt":"He always wears a coat, ___ in hot weather.","options":["still","even","yet","already"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Kutilmagan/hayratlanarli holatni ta'kidlash uchun 'even' ishlatiladi: even in hot weather (hatto issiq havoda ham)."},{"id":"u113","unit":113,"section":"Conjunctions and prepositions","unitTitle":"although/though/even though, in spite of/despite","prompt":"___ the rain, we enjoyed our walk.","options":["Although","Despite","Even though","Because"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Despite/in spite of' dan keyin ot yoki -ing keladi (bog'lovchi gap emas): despite the rain. 'Although' dan keyin esa to'liq gap keladi."},{"id":"u114","unit":114,"section":"Conjunctions and prepositions","unitTitle":"in case","prompt":"I'll leave my phone on ___ Jack calls.","options":["if","in case","unless","when"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'In case' — ehtiyot chorasi, ehtimoliy holat uchun oldindan tayyorgarlik ma'nosini beradi: in case Jack calls (agar qo'ng'iroq qilsa deb)."},{"id":"u115","unit":115,"section":"Conjunctions and prepositions","unitTitle":"unless, as long as, provided","prompt":"I'll come to the party ___ I have to work late.","options":["unless","as long as","provided","in case"],"correct":0,"explanation":"'Unless' = 'if...not': agar ishlashga to'g'ri kelmasa (ishlamasam) boraman."},{"id":"u116","unit":116,"section":"Conjunctions and prepositions","unitTitle":"as (as I walked … / as I was …)","prompt":"___ I was walking home, it started to rain.","options":["While","During","As","For"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Ikki harakat bir vaqtda sodir bo'lganda 'as' (o'sha payt/paytda) bog'lovchisi ishlatilishi mumkin."},{"id":"u117","unit":117,"section":"Conjunctions and prepositions","unitTitle":"like and as","prompt":"___ I said before, I really think we should wait.","options":["Like","As","Such as","Alike"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'As I said' — jumla shaklidagi qurilmalarda ('...gandek') 'as' ishlatiladi, 'like' emas."},{"id":"u118","unit":118,"section":"Conjunctions and prepositions","unitTitle":"like / as if","prompt":"She's a great singer. She sings ___ she was a professional.","options":["like","as","as if","such as"],"correct":2,"explanation":"'Look/sound/seem/feel + as if' — go'yo, xuddi shundaydek ma'noni beradi: sings as if she was a professional."},{"id":"u119","unit":119,"section":"Conjunctions and prepositions","unitTitle":"during, for, while","prompt":"I fell asleep ___ the movie.","options":["while","during","for","meanwhile"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'During' dan keyin ot (the movie) keladi. 'While' esa ergash gap (subject+verb) bilan ishlatiladi."},{"id":"u120","unit":120,"section":"Conjunctions and prepositions","unitTitle":"by and until, by the time …","prompt":"I have to finish this report ___ Friday.","options":["until","by","during","since"],"correct":1,"explanation":"Ma'lum muddatgacha bir marta bajarilishi kerak bo'lgan harakat uchun 'by' ishlatiladi (Juma kunigacha tugatilishi kerak)."},{"id":"u121","unit":121,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"at/on/in (time)","prompt":"My birthday is ___ 5 April.","options":["at","in","on","by"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Aniq kunlar va sanalar bilan 'on' ishlatiladi: on 5 April."},{"id":"u122","unit":122,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"on time / in time, at the end / in the end","prompt":"The train departed ___ time — not a minute late.","options":["on","in","at","by"],"correct":0,"explanation":"'On time' — aniq belgilangan vaqtda, kechikmasdan degan ma'noni beradi."},{"id":"u123","unit":123,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"in/at/on (position) 1","prompt":"When I arrived, David was waiting ___ the corner of the street.","options":["in","on","at","by"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Aniq nuqta (burchak, chorraha) haqida gapirganda 'at' ishlatiladi: at the corner."},{"id":"u124","unit":124,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"in/at/on (position) 2","prompt":"I read about it ___ the newspaper this morning.","options":["at","on","in","by"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Gazeta, kitob, xat kabi yozma manbalar ichida degan ma'noda 'in' ishlatiladi: in the newspaper."},{"id":"u125","unit":125,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"in/at/on (position) 3","prompt":"I saw an old friend of mine ___ the bus this morning.","options":["at","in","on","by"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Jamoat transporti (bus/train/plane) ichida bo'lish uchun 'on' ishlatiladi: on the bus."},{"id":"u126","unit":126,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"to, at, in and into","prompt":"What time did you arrive ___ the airport?","options":["to","at","into","in"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Arrive at' — kichikroq joy/nuqta (airport, hotel, station) uchun ishlatiladi; katta joy/mamlakat uchun esa 'arrive in'."},{"id":"u127","unit":127,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"in/on/at (other uses)","prompt":"Is there anything good ___ TV tonight?","options":["at","in","on","by"],"correct":2,"explanation":"'On TV / on the radio' — efirda, translyatsiyada degan ma'noda turg'un ishlatiladigan predlog birikmasi."},{"id":"u128","unit":128,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"by","prompt":"Do you usually go to work ___ car?","options":["with","in","by","on"],"correct":2,"explanation":"Transport turini bildirishda 'by' ishlatiladi: by car/by bus/by train (lekin: on foot)."},{"id":"u129","unit":129,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"Noun + preposition (reason for, cause of)","prompt":"What was the reason ___ the delay?","options":["of","for","from","with"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Reason for something' — turg'un birikma: the reason for the delay."},{"id":"u130","unit":130,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"Adjective + preposition 1 (nice of, kind to)","prompt":"It was very kind ___ you to help me carry these bags.","options":["from","of","with","to"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Nice/kind/generous/stupid + OF + somebody (to do something)' — xulq-atvorni baholashda: kind of you."},{"id":"u131","unit":131,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"Adjective + preposition 2 (afraid of, married to)","prompt":"Are you ___ spiders?","options":["afraid with","afraid from","afraid of","afraid for"],"correct":2,"explanation":"'Afraid of something/somebody' — nimadan qo'rqish predlogi doim 'of'."},{"id":"u132","unit":132,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"Verb + preposition 1: to and at","prompt":"Please listen carefully ___ what I'm going to say.","options":["at","to","for","with"],"correct":1,"explanation":"'Listen to something/somebody' — turg'un fe'l+predlog birikmasi."},{"id":"u133","unit":133,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"Verb + preposition 2: about/for/of/after","prompt":"Can you look ___ my cat while I'm away?","options":["after","for","at","of"],"correct":0,"explanation":"'Look after somebody/something' — g'amxo'rlik qilmoq, qaramoq ma'nosidagi turg'un birikma."},{"id":"u134","unit":134,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"Verb + preposition 3: about and of","prompt":"I've never heard ___ that band before.","options":["for","about","of","from"],"correct":2,"explanation":"'Hear of somebody/something' — birovning/narsaning mavjudligidan xabardor bo'lish: never heard of that band."},{"id":"u135","unit":135,"section":"Prepositions","unitTitle":"Verb + preposition 4: of/for/from/on","prompt":"The number of road accidents has increased. This is mainly due ___ the volume of traffic.","options":["of","for","to","from"],"correct":2,"explanation":"'Due to something' — sabab bo'lishi ma'nosidagi turg'un birikma."},{"id":"u136","unit":136,"section":